children.value: What is mongocli?

The MongoDB CLI is a modern command line interface that enables you to manage
your MongoDB services from the terminal.
View installation instructions
Manage your Deployment from the Command Line
Use simple, one-line commands to interact with MongoDB
Atlas
Cloud Manager

Ops Manager

Atlas

Create a Profile

Store your API keys, organization and project IDs, and other

To learn more, see Configure the MongoDB CLI
